<h2 id="electricity">Electricity</h2>

<ul>
  <li>
    <p>Ampere: A - base unit. Attractive/repulsive force of \(2 \times 10^{-7}\) Newtons between
two wires 1m appart is the definition of  \(1\,\mathrm{A}\).
\(1\,\mathrm{A} = 1\,\mathrm{C} / 1\,\mathrm{s}\)</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Coulomb: C -  charge transported by a constant current of 1 A in on second.
\(1\,\mathrm{C} = 1\,\mathrm{A} \cdot 1\,\mathrm{s}\)</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p><a href="http://hyperphysics.phy-astr.gsu.edu/hbase/electric/elewor.html">Electrical work</a> is the work done on a charged particle by an electric field.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Watt : W - power.  \(1\,\mathrm{W} = \frac{1\,\mathrm{N} \cdot \mathrm{m}}{\mathrm{s}}\)</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Volt: V - pressure</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Ohm: \(\Omega\) - electrical resistance</p>
  </li>
</ul>

<h3 id="voltage">voltage</h3>

\[V = \frac{\mathrm{potential energy}}{\mathrm{charge}} = \frac{N\cdot m}{C}\]

<h3 id="ohm">Ohm</h3>

<ul>
  <li>Ah - ampere hour</li>
  <li>mAh - milli ampere hour</li>
</ul>
